而每一个像素里包含超过150万个橘子。

82
00:03:55.216 --> 00:03:57.188
So how big of a telescope do we need
所以，我们需要多大的望远镜

83
00:03:57.212 --> 00:03:59.977
in order to see an orange on the surface of the moon
才能看到月球表面的橘子，

84
00:04:00.001 --> 00:04:02.215
and, by extension, our black hole?
以及，那个黑洞呢？

85
00:04:02.239 --> 00:04:04.579
Well, it turns out that by crunching the numbers,
事实上，通过计算，

86
00:04:03.975 --> 00:04:06.537
you can easily calculate that we would need a telescope
我们可以轻易得出所需的 望远镜的大小，

87
00:04:06.537 --> 00:04:07.984
the size of the entire Earth.
就和整个地球一样大。

88
00:04:07.984 --> 00:04:08.882
(Laughter)
（笑声）

89
00:04:08.882 --> 00:04:11.065
If we could build this Earth-sized telescope,
而如果我们能够建造出这个 地球大小的望远镜，

90
00:04:11.845 --> 00:04:14.770
we could just start to make out that distinctive ring of light
就能够分辨出那指示着视界线的

91
00:04:13.894 --> 00:04:16.331
indicative of the black hole's event horizon.
独特的光环。

92
00:04:16.331 --> 00:04:19.273
Although this picture wouldn't contain all the detail we see
尽管在这张照片上，我们无法看到

93
00:04:19.943 --> 00:04:21.449
in computer graphic renderings,
电脑合成图上的那些细节，

94
00:04:20.923 --> 00:04:23.406
it would allow us to safely get our first glimpse
它仍可以让我们对于

95
00:04:23.796 --> 00:04:26.283
of the immediate environment around a black hole.
黑洞周围的环境有个大致的了解。

96
00:04:26.307 --> 00:04:27.920
However, as you can imagine,
但是，正如你预料，

97
00:04:27.944 --> 00:04:31.568
building a single-dish telescope the size of the Earth is impossible.
想建造一个地球大小的射电望远镜 是不可能的。

98
00:04:31.592 --> 00:04:33.479
But in the famous words of Mick Jagger,
不过，米克·贾格尔有一句名言：

99
00:04:33.503 --> 00:04:35.294
"You can't always get what you want,
“你不可能永远心想事成，

100
00:04:35.318 --> 00:04:37.505
but if you try sometimes, you just might find
但如果你尝试了，说不定就 正好能找到

101
00:04:37.529 --> 00:04:38.744
